Intents in Android allow you to send messages, trigger other activities and applications. This mechanism can work both within the same application and between applications. Application examples: launching an activity or service to perform certain actions event notification explicit launch of the specified service or activity The explicit intent contains a call to a certain (pre-known) class. When using explicit intent, the following are specified: the context from which the call will be made the class of the called component (service or activity) additional information (extras), if necessaryn
